<subSubSection pageId="91" pageNumber="149" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="91.[715,1312,2810,3233]" pageId="91" pageNumber="149">
F. C. Almeida and colleagues in 2014 provided evidence of 4-7% sequence divergence in cytochrome-b between former subspecies 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1876" box="[872,1009,3082,3115]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Pteropus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Chiroptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="149" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="capistratus">capistratus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Flannery &amp; White" authorityYear="1991" box="[1077,1171,3082,3115]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="Pleropus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="91" pageNumber="149" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ennisae">ennisae</taxonomicName>
. Morphological differences also support distinction at the species level. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Flannery &amp; White" authorityYear="1991" box="[1016,1233,3161,3194]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Pteropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="149" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ennisae">Pteropus ennisae</taxonomicName>
is in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1876" box="[772,909,3204,3233]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Pteropus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Chiroptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="149" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="capistratus">capistratus</taxonomicName>
species group. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[102,837,3238,3271]" pageId="91" pageNumber="149" type="distribution">
